# Production Standard

Authoritative detail: `Documents/04_Production/ProductionPlaybook.md`.

## Definition of Done

A mission is done only when applicable gates pass:

- Blueprint compile PASS
- Technical Simulate / runtime checks PASS
- **Human** PIE Gameplay PASS (or EP written waiver) — Technical ≠ Gameplay
- Replay PASS if replay is claimed (full world + player reverse)
- Documentation updated (mission notes + Changelog append)
- Naming / folders per DOC-002 / ASSET-001
- Mission Completion Report submitted with honest PASS / FAIL / N/A
- Git commit / push when requested; never push failing code

Do not mark Ready For Review YES if compile, required runtime, or docs are incomplete.

## Honest Gates

- Enhanced Input cannot be fully driven by Slate/MCP automation — do not claim Gameplay PASS from Technical-only evidence.
- Tag PrintString audio / mesh stand-ins as debt; do not claim Production Ready on placeholders alone.
- Incomplete SliceReset → do not claim Replay PASS.

## SliceReset

If the mission claims replay without UE restart, reverse everything the loop mutates: doors, lights, Witness, PowerManager flags, ambient once-flags, notes, objectives, pickups/respawns, generator/puzzle state as applicable.

## Technical Debt

Triage in `Documents/02_Technical/Architecture/TechnicalDebt.md`. Prefer dedicated cleanup missions. Do not expand core frameworks outside brief scope.

